claim.claim-text:
6. A battery system comprising:
a positive contactor connected between a positive electrode of a battery pack and a first output end;
a negative contactor connected between a negative electrode of the battery pack and a second output end;
a main controller is configured to control the positive contactor and the negative contactor to be opened and closed, and to generate a fusion bonding sensing signal according to whether the positive contactor is fused and bonded; and
a fusion bonding protecting module configured to control the negative contactor according to a control signal received from the main controller when a voltage difference between a first end and a second end of the positive contactor is equal to or greater than a predetermined threshold value, and to maintain the negative contactor to be opened irrespective of the control signal when the voltage difference is less than the predetermined threshold value.
